cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a new convolutional neural network architecture for image recognition tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also focuses on improving information flow and utilizing parameters more efficiently, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The recurrent feedback structure used in the proposed architecture also suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed models on image recognition datasets, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
